text: I have a general 3D printing question. I am looking to permanently embed an M8 or larger nut in a printed part. I need more than just a press fit. Is there a way to add the nut and continue printing over it? Is there another method I should look at? Thanks

elements.text: I have a general 3D printing question. I am looking to permanently embed an M8 or larger nut in a printed part. I need more than just a press fit. Is there a way to add the nut and continue printing over it? Is there another method I should look at? Thanks

text: Heat-set inserts? Alternatively you can make a two-part design that get clamped together with smaller fasteners and then fully enclose the M8 nut

elements.text: Heat-set inserts? Alternatively you can make a two-part design that get clamped together with smaller fasteners and then fully enclose the M8 nut
